<br>
The game is ok, but it's so buggy that any pvp action with guild vs guild means you will crash to desktop when more than 20 people come onto your screen. Then you will sit at the character select for 20 minutes and crash again when you get in.  When you are in and aren't raiding or whatnot, you will experience constant lag. A 0.5 second casting hide skill will usually take around 15 seconds to cast. This is normal, you are always lagged and the servers will very often freeze up for 5 minutes or so where you cannot even move before they crash (as they do every single night) where you often get roll backs. After three weeks of rollbacks and server downs where you can go days without even being able to log in DO expect them to grace your account with a free 3 days of playing, at a whopping savings of $0.75 to your credit card.<br>
<br>
Ubisoft servers are single handedly the worst piece of shit servers I have ever played a game on, including the ubisoft eq server Kane Bayle. Avoid these guys like a bad case of herpies, they have no clue how to run their servers and not a single thing has been done that has even moderately fixed this since the game was released.<br>
<br>
Establishing a nation.<br>
Good luck, the beta guilds all control their servers and the result has been a very &quot;un-pvp&quot; game where zerg alliances and nations simply run the server and pvp is a rare thing to find, short of Timmy Griefer running around pking noobs. Forget it if you had dreams of running around with an elite fighting force, the game is all about numbers, zerging, and having 50+ people online to defend your town at 4am on monday morning.<br>
<br>
